Please read each item and think about this student's behavior during the past two months. Then, decide how often this student displays the behavior. If this student never exhibits the behavior, choose “N”. If this student seldom exhibits the behavior, choose “S”. If this student often exhibits the behavior, choose “O”.If this student almost always exhibits the behavior, choose “A”.

For each of the Social Skills items, please also rate how important you think the behavior is for success in your classroom. If you think the behavior is not important for success in your classroom, choose “N”. If you think the behavior is important for success in your classroom, choose “I”. If you think the behavior is critical for success in your classroom, choose “C”.

Mark "5" if this student is in the highest 10% of the class. Lowest 10%= 1, Next Lowest 20%= 2, Middle 40%= 3, Next Highest 20%= 4, Highest 10%= 5.
